(364, 1, '2007-01-04 14:55:53', '2007-01-04 14:55:53', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\nZ. Xu and K. L. Shepard, "<a href="/wp-content/uploads/2017/04/3.pdf" target="_blank">Low-jitter active deskewing through injection-locked resonant clocking</a>" IEEE Custom Integrated Circuits Conference, 2007.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nActive deskewing is an important technique for managing variability in clock distributions but introduces latency and power-supply-noise sensitivity to the resulting networks. In this paper, we demonstrate how active deskewing can be achieved with resonant distributions without introducing significant jitter. The prototype network operates at a nominal 2-GHz frequency in a 0.18m CMOS technology with more than 25 pF/mm2 of clock loading.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'Low-jitter active deskewing through injection-locked resonant clocking', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'low-jitter-active-deskewing-through-injection-locked-resonant-clocking', '', '', '2017-04-04 18:41:05', '2017-04-04 18:41:05', '', 0, 'http://bioee.dev/?p=364', 0, 'post', '', 0),
