(637, 1, '2013-01-04 18:55:52', '2013-01-04 18:55:52', 'Xuetao Gan, Ren-Jye Shiue, Yuanda Gao, Inanc Meric, Tony F. Heinz, Kenneth Shepard, James Hone, Solomon Assefa &amp; Dirk Englund, "<a href="http://www.nature.com/nphoton/journal/vaop/ncurrent/abs/nphoton.2013.253.html" target="_blank">Chip-integrated ultrafast graphene photodetector with high responsivity</a>" Nature Photonics (2013) doi:10.1038/nphoton.2013.253', 'Chip-integrated ultrafast graphene photodetector with high responsivity', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'chip-integrated-ultrafast-graphene-photodetector-with-high-responsivity', '', '', '2017-04-05 19:54:18', '2017-04-05 19:54:18', '', 0, 'http://bioee.dev/?p=637', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(638, 1, '2013-01-04 18:38:12', '2013-01-04 18:38:12', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']\r\nR. M. Field and K. L. Shepard, "<a href="/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Field_Shepard-VLSI_FLIM.pdf" target="_blank">A 100-fps Fluorescence Lifetime Imager in Standard 0.13-m CMOS,</a>" Symposium on VLSI Circuits, 2013.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nA wide-field fluorescence lifetime imager capable of up to 100 frames per second (fps) is presented. The imager consists of a64-by-64 array of low-noise single photon avalanche diodes (SPADs) in a standard 0.13-micron CMOS process, 4096 time-to- digital converters, and an application specific data path to enable continuous image acquisition at a total output data rate of 42 Gbps. These features combine to enable new lifetime-based diagnostic imaging.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'A 100-fps Fluorescence Lifetime Imager in Standard 0.13-m CMOS', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'a-100-fps-fluorescence-lifetime-imager-in-standard-0-13-%ce%bcm-cmos', '', '', '2017-04-05 19:30:31', '2017-04-05 19:30:31', '', 0, 'http://bioee.dev/?p=638', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(639, 1, '2017-04-05 13:39:01', '2017-04-05 13:39:01', 'Xuetao Gan, Ren-Jye Shiue, Yuanda Gao, Inanc Meric, Tony F. Heinz, Kenneth Shepard, James Hone, Solomon Assefa &amp; Dirk Englund, "<a href="http://www.nature.com/nphoton/journal/vaop/ncurrent/abs/nphoton.2013.253.html" target="_blank">Chip-integrated ultrafast graphene photodetector with high responsivity</a>" Nature Photonics (2013) doi:10.1038/nphoton.2013.253', 'Chip-integrated ultrafast graphene photodetector with high responsivity', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '637-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-05 13:39:01', '2017-04-05 13:39:01', '', 637, 'http://bioee.dev/637-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(640, 1, '2017-04-05 13:40:28', '2017-04-05 13:40:28', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\nR. M. Field and K. L. Shepard, "<a href="https://www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu/downloads/2013/Field_Shepard-VLSI_FLIM.pdf" target="_blank">A 100-fps Fluorescence Lifetime Imager in Standard 0.13-m CMOS,</a>" Symposium on VLSI Circuits, 2013.\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nA wide-field fluorescence lifetime imager capable of up to 100 frames per second (fps) is presented. The imager consists of a64-by-64 array of low-noise single photon avalanche diodes (SPADs) in a standard 0.13-micron CMOS process, 4096 time-to- digital converters, and an application specific data path to enable continuous image acquisition at a total output data rate of 42 Gbps. These features combine to enable new lifetime-based diagnostic imaging.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'A 100-fps Fluorescence Lifetime Imager in Standard 0.13-m CMOS', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '638-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-05 13:40:28', '2017-04-05 13:40:28', '', 638, 'http://bioee.dev/638-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(641, 1, '2013-01-04 18:30:32', '2013-01-04 18:30:32', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']\r\nRyan P. Davies, ChengCheng, Noah Sturcken, William E. Bailey, and Kenneth L. Shepard, "<a href="/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/06559026.pdf" target="_blank">Coupled Inductors With Crossed Anisotropy CoZrTz/SiO<sub>2</sub>Multilayer Cores</a>," IEEE Transactions On Magnetics, Vol. 49, No. 7, July 2013\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nFour-turn coupled (flux-closed) inductor structures have been fabricated and tested for use in high-power-density integrated voltage regulator (IVR) applications. Our solenoid-like structure is comprised of a laminated magnetic core of four rungs surrounded by four Cu windings creating four coupled inductors. The magnetic core is made of laminations of ultra-high-vacuum-sputtered [5 nm Ta/200 nm Co<sub>91.5</sub>Zr<sub>4.0</sub>Ta<sub>4.5</sub> (CZT)/7 nm SiO<sub>2</sub> ] repeated 20 times. Individual CZT layers are deposited under a magnetic bias to induce uniaxial anisotropy. The quad-coupled inductor shows a frequency response with a measured self-inductance of 7.4 nH for one inductor sustained up to 100 MHz and roll-off to half this low-frequency value at ~450MHz. This inductance is more than 65X higher than what would be calculated from an air-core inductor of equivalent geometry.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'Coupled Inductors With Crossed Anisotropy CoZrTz/SiO2Multilayer Cores', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'coupled-inductors-with-crossed-anisotropy-cozrtzsio2multilayer-cores', '', '', '2017-04-05 19:31:44', '2017-04-05 19:31:44', '', 0, 'http://bioee.dev/?p=641', 0, 'post', '', 0),
(642, 1, '2017-04-05 13:41:58', '2017-04-05 13:41:58', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\']\r\nRyan P. Davies, ChengCheng, Noah Sturcken, William E. Bailey, and Kenneth L. Shepard, "<a href="https://www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu/downloads/2013/06559026.pdf" target="_blank">Coupled Inductors With Crossed Anisotropy CoZrTz/SiO<sub>2</sub>Multilayer Cores</a>," IEEE Transactions On Magnetics, Vol. 49, No. 7, July 2013\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nFour-turn coupled (flux-closed) inductor structures have been fabricated and tested for use in high-power-density integrated voltage regulator (IVR) applications. Our solenoid-like structure is comprised of a laminated magnetic core of four rungs surrounded by four Cu windings creating four coupled inductors. The magnetic core is made of laminations of ultra-high-vacuum-sputtered [5 nm Ta/200 nm Co<sub>91.5</sub>Zr<sub>4.0</sub>Ta<sub>4.5</sub> (CZT)/7 nm SiO<sub>2</sub> ] repeated 20 times. Individual CZT layers are deposited under a magnetic bias to induce uniaxial anisotropy. The quad-coupled inductor shows a frequency response with a measured self-inductance of 7.4 nH for one inductor sustained up to 100 MHz and roll-off to half this low-frequency value at ~450MHz. This inductance is more than 65X higher than what would be calculated from an air-core inductor of equivalent geometry.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'Coupled Inductors With Crossed Anisotropy CoZrTz/SiO2Multilayer Cores', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '641-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-05 13:41:58', '2017-04-05 13:41:58', '', 641, 'http://bioee.dev/641-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(643, 1, '2017-04-05 18:41:04', '2017-04-05 18:41:04', '', '06724568', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'closed', '', '06724568', '', '', '2017-04-05 18:41:04', '2017-04-05 18:41:04', '', 605, 'http://bioee.dev/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/06724568.pdf', 0, 'attachment', 'application/pdf', 0),
(644, 1, '2017-04-05 18:42:21', '2017-04-05 18:42:21', '[av_one_full first min_height=\'\' vertical_alignment=\'\' space=\'\' custom_margin=\'\' margin=\'0px\' padding=\'0px\' border=\'\' border_color=\'\' radius=\'0px\' background_color=\'\' src=\'\' background_position=\'top left\' background_repeat=\'no-repeat\' animation=\'\' mobile_display=\'\']\r\n\r\n[av_textblock size=\'\' font_color=\'\' color=\'\' admin_preview_bg=\'\']\r\nRakheja, S.; Han Wang; Palacios, T.; Meric, I.; Shepard, K.; Antoniadis, D., "<a href="/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/06724568.pdf" target="_blank">A unified charge-current compact model for ambipolar operation in quasi-ballistic graphene transistors: Experimental verification and circuit-analysis demonstration,</a>" Electron Devices Meeting (IEDM), 2013 IEEE International , vol., no., pp.5.5.1,5.5.4, 9-11 Dec. 2013\r\n[/av_textblock]\r\n\r\n[/av_one_full][av_toggle_container initial=\'0\' mode=\'accordion\' sort=\'\']\r\n[av_toggle title=\'Abstract\' tags=\'\']\r\nThis paper presents a compact virtual source (VS) model to describe carrier transport valid in both unipolar and ambipolar transport regimes in quasi-ballistic graphene fieldeffect transistors (GFETs). The model formulation allows for an easy extension to bi-layer graphene transistors, where a bandgap can be opened. The model also includes descriptions of intrinsic terminal charges/capacitances obtained selfconsistently with the transport formulation. The charge model extends from drift-diffusive transport regime to ballistic transport regime, where gradual-channel approximation (GCA) fails. The model is calibrated exhaustively against DC and S-parameter measurements of GFETs. To demonstrate the model capability for circuit-level simulations, the Verilog-A implementation of the model is used to simulate the dynamic response of frequency doubling circuits with GFETs operating in the ambipolar regime.\r\n[/av_toggle]\r\n[/av_toggle_container]', 'A unified charge-current compact model for ambipolar operation in quasi-ballistic graphene transistors: Experimental verification and circuit-analysis demonstration', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '605-revision-v1', '', '', '2017-04-05 18:42:21', '2017-04-05 18:42:21', '', 605, 'http://bioee.dev/605-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
