(1149, 1, '2013-08-01 17:26:07', '2013-08-01 17:26:07', 'An interdisciplinary team of researchers from Columbia University, led by <a href="http://www.bioee.ee.columbia.edu/~shepard/">Ken Shepard</a>, professor of electrical engineering and biomedical engineering at Columbia Engineering and including <a href="http://www.columbia.edu/cu/chemistry/groups/cornish/">Virginia W. Cornish</a>, Helena Rubinstein Professor of Chemistry, and <a href="http://www.dietrichlab.com/">Lars Dietrich</a>, assistant professor of biological sciences, has won a prestigious $1 million three-year grant from the W. M. Keck Foundation to advance their research in combining biological components with solid-state electronics, creating new systems that exploit the advantages of both.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://engineering.columbia.edu/columbia-researchers-win-1-million-keck-award" target="_blank">Learn More</a>', 'Columbia Researchers Win $1 Million Keck Award!', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'columbia-researchers-win-1-million-keck-award', '', '', '2017-04-11 17:15:25', '2017-04-11 17:15:25', '', 0, 'http://bioee.dev/?p=1149', 0, 'post', '', 0),
